The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 16: Power regulator CERC has unveiled new norms for inter-state transmission of power, based on the distance and direction of electricity, which will result in lowering of tariffs in the long term. The regulations will implement the point-of-connection method of sharing the cost of inter-state transmission services. Earlier, states were charged a uniform fee for inter-state power transmission in the form of postage stamps, irrespective of the distance.                            
	 Mumbai, June 16: The government will prematurely buy back three types of bonds worth up to Rs 20,000 crore beginning Friday, as liquidity has come under pressure because of much higher 3G and broadband spectrum licence fees, and the first quarter advance tax.                            
	 Mumbai, June 16: The State Bank of India (SBI) plans to foray into wealth management this fiscal to tap high networth clients. The bank is also scouting for a global partner for its merchant acquiring business.                            
	 New Delhi, June 16: The coal ministry is considering a 10 per cent further equity dilution in Neyveli Lignite Corporation, a move which may mobilise about Rs 2,400 crore for the exchequer.                            
	 Mumbai, June 16: Credit growth of banks stood at 19 per cent during the one-year period ended June 4 against 15.10 per cent a year ago.
                                                                                                                          
